<p><a name="Films_.26_Games" id="Films_.26_Games"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Terry_Riley&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Films &amp; Games">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Films &amp; Games</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>1976 - <i>Music With Roots in the Aether: Opera for Television</i>. Tape 6: Terry Riley. Produced and directed by <a href="/wiki/Robert_Ashley" title="Robert Ashley">Robert Ashley</a>. New York, New York: Lovely Music.</li>
<li>1986 - <a href="http://otherminds.org/shop/Notes.html" class="external text" title="http://otherminds.org/shop/Notes.html" rel="nofollow"><i>In Between the Notes...a Portrait of Pandit Pran Nath, Master Indian Musician</i></a>. Produced by <a href="/wiki/Other_Minds" title="Other Minds">Other Minds</a>, directed by <a href="/wiki/William_Farley" title="William Farley">William Farley</a>.</li>
<li>1995 - <i>Musical Outsiders: An American Legacy - Harry Partch, Lou Harrison, and Terry Riley</i>. Directed by Michael Blackwood.</li>
<li>2008 - "A Rainbow In Curved Air" features in the in-game soundtrack of Grand Theft Auto IV. It can be found when listening to the fictional radio station, "The Journey".</li>
</ul>
